JS Site Crit Team Post


30 Jun 2019 15:43






While this is a good premise and there's horror here to be found, this was a -1 from me. As it stands, there are some issues with the tone and this article just comes out and hits you in the face with a lot of its details, like the ripping off the skin bit. In addition, there are several spots throughout where the author has chosen to bring in  and other such strong and generally non-clinical language.

Why is the spleen being removed? I see later in the article that this appears to be the seat of the spore production so that makes sense, but if someone has a fungal infection, removing the spleen is likely a death sentence.





