28 Apr 2020 06:04






Short and sweet SCP, I enjoyed it.

I'd advise going over the interview log again, though. Making the subject appear actually stupid is gonna be way harder than it's worth, I think. . This implies that the identity was wiped off the record entirely. Or, it might even be a better idea to make up a name like Karliah Jones and replace that same number of characters with full block icons. Up to you.

Hell, I'd remove the whole IQ lowering thing overall and make the person behave as if they're normal but memory-wiped and suddenly outside the control of their actions. I think that'd be scarier, anyways.

Also, as another commenter said, removing the spleen, in particular, seems a bit unnecessary. Writing  in a clinical tone is a perfectly acceptable containment measure.







